01:56:34,988 --> 01:56:36,740
You've made quite a life for yourself.

1477
01:56:36,907 --> 01:56:37,949
Hmm.

1478
01:56:38,116 --> 01:56:41,244
- You should be very proud.
- Shut the fuck up, you piece of shit.

1479
01:56:54,925 --> 01:56:56,343
<i>Someone lost contact, copy.</i>

1480
01:57:08,939 --> 01:57:10,398
California, stay away from here.

1481
01:57:10,565 --> 01:57:13,026
Stay away from here, now.
Don't come in here.

1482
01:57:13,485 --> 01:57:15,195
<i>Whatever you hear, stay away.</i>

1483
01:57:16,404 --> 01:57:19,491
John Doe has the upper hand. Mills!

1484
01:57:19,908 --> 01:57:21,034
Here he comes.

1485
01:57:21,201 --> 01:57:23,078
- Throw your gun down!
- What?

1486
01:57:23,245 --> 01:57:25,455
- I wish I could've lived like you.
- Shut up.

1487
01:57:25,622 --> 01:57:28,416
- What the fuck you talking about?
- Go away!

1488
01:57:28,583 --> 01:57:29,876
Do you hear me, detective?

1489
01:57:30,043 --> 01:57:34,381
I'm trying to tell you how much
I admire you and your pretty wife.

1490
01:57:35,465 --> 01:57:37,300
- What?
- Tracy.

1491
01:57:37,467 --> 01:57:38,677
Mills!

1492
01:57:38,843 --> 01:57:39,928
What'd you fucking say?

1493
01:57:40,095 --> 01:57:44,182
It's disturbing how easily a member
of the press can purchase information...

1494
01:57:44,349 --> 01:57:46,059
...from the men in your precinct.

1495
01:57:46,560 --> 01:57:48,061
What the fuck?

1496
01:57:48,478 --> 01:57:50,355
<i>Throw your gun down!</i>

1497
01:57:50,522 --> 01:57:52,566
I visited your home this morning...

1498
01:57:53,567 --> 01:57:55,360
After you'd left.

1499
01:57:55,527 --> 01:57:57,654
- Mills!
- I tried to play husband.

1500
01:57:58,321 --> 01:58:01,575
I tried to taste the life of a simple man.

1501
01:58:01,783 --> 01:58:03,034
Throw it away!

1502
01:58:03,201 --> 01:58:05,495
Tsk, it didn't work out.

1503
01:58:05,662 --> 01:58:07,330
So...

1504
01:58:07,497 --> 01:58:09,416
I took a souvenir.

1505
01:58:11,042 --> 01:58:12,752
Her pretty head.

1506
01:58:12,919 --> 01:58:14,504
Mills.

1507
01:58:15,046 --> 01:58:16,673
Mills.

1508
01:58:17,674 --> 01:58:18,842
What's he talking about?

1509
01:58:19,009 --> 01:58:21,386
- Give me your gun.
- What's going on over there?

1510
01:58:21,553 --> 01:58:22,846
Put the, ugh-- Put the gun down.

1511
01:58:23,013 --> 01:58:25,015
I saw you with a box.
What was in the box?

1512
01:58:25,181 --> 01:58:28,101
- Because I envy your normal life.
- Put the gun down, David.

1513
01:58:28,268 --> 01:58:31,229
- It seems that envy is my sin.
- Oh, what's in the box?

1514
01:58:31,396 --> 01:58:33,732
- Not until you give me the gun.
- What's in the box?

1515
01:58:33,898 --> 01:58:35,650
- Give me the gun.
- He just told you.

1516
01:58:35,817 --> 01:58:39,446
- You lie. You're a fucking liar, shut up.
- David.

1517
01:58:39,613 --> 01:58:42,365
That's what he wants.
He wants you to shoot him.

1518
01:58:42,532 --> 01:58:45,660
No! No.

1519
01:58:46,036 --> 01:58:47,829
You tell me that's not true.

1520
01:58:47,996 --> 01:58:50,123
- That's not true.
- Become vengeance, David.

1521
01:58:50,290 --> 01:58:53,168
- Oh, she's all right. You tell me.
- Become...

1522
01:58:53,335 --> 01:58:55,837
- ...wrath.
- Tell me she's all right!

1523
01:58:56,004 --> 01:58:58,131
- If you murder a suspect, David--
- No.

1524
01:58:58,298 --> 01:59:00,050
You throw it all away, he knows it.

1525
01:59:00,216 --> 01:59:01,217
No!

1526
01:59:01,384 --> 01:59:03,386
- She begged for her life.
- Shut up.

1527
01:59:03,553 --> 01:59:07,223
She begged for her life
and for the life of the baby inside of her.

1528
01:59:23,281 --> 01:59:24,658
Oh.

1529
01:59:26,576 --> 01:59:27,786
He didn't know.

1530
01:59:41,758 --> 01:59:43,718
Give me the gun, David.

1531
01:59:48,682 --> 01:59:50,183
David.

1532
01:59:51,476 --> 01:59:52,894
If you kill him...

1533
01:59:54,396 --> 01:59:56,147
...he will win.

1534
01:59:59,859 --> 02:00:01,695
Oh, God.

1535
02:00:01,861 --> 02:00:04,072
Oh, God.

1536
02:00:04,781 --> 02:00:05,949
Oh!

1537
02:00:19,379 --> 02:00:21,131
Oh, fuck, he shot him.

1538
02:00:43,236 --> 02:00:45,822
<i>Set it down somewhere.</i>

1539
02:00:47,031 --> 02:00:49,325
<i>Come on, set us down.</i>

1540
02:00:51,745 --> 02:00:55,540
<i>Holy Christ. Somebody call somebody.</i>

1541
02:00:55,707 --> 02:00:57,542
<i>Call somebody.</i>

1542
02:01:12,015 --> 02:01:15,059
Well, we'll take care of him.

1543
02:01:23,735 --> 02:01:25,779
Whatever he needs.

1544
02:01:26,696 --> 02:01:28,198
Where are you gonna be?

1545
02:01:30,909 --> 02:01:32,285
Around.

1546
02:01:36,623 --> 02:01:38,541
I'll be around.

1547
02:01:42,420 --> 02:01:44,672
<i>Ernest Hemingway once wrote:</i>

1548
02:01:44,839 --> 02:01:49,260
<i>"The world is a fine place
and worth fighting for."</i>

1549
02:01:50,094 --> 02:01:52,680
<i>I agree with the second part.</i>
